[
{ type: install
  message: <<EOM
x201t-wacomd has been installed.

This daemon is intended for the Lenovo ThinkPad X201 Tablet internal
serial Wacom ISDv4 pen digitizer.

Typical setup:

  sysrc x201t_wacomd_enable=YES
  sysrc x201t_wacomd_device=/dev/cuau2
  sysrc x201t_wacomd_baud=19200
  service x201t_wacomd start

Optional tty console pointer support:

  sysrc x201t_wacomd_console_enable=YES
  sysrc x201t_wacomd_console_mode=absolute
  sysrc x201t_wacomd_console_width=1280
  sysrc x201t_wacomd_console_height=800
  sysrc x201t_wacomd_console_scale=32
  sysrc x201t_wacomd_console_eraser_mode=scroll
  sysrc x201t_wacomd_console_eraser_scroll_scale=768
  service x201t_wacomd restart

The console backend writes FreeBSD console mouse events to /dev/consolectl.
It works independently from Xorg. The rc.d script also runs vidcontrol -m on
for /dev/ttyv* when console mode is enabled so the text-console pointer is
visible.

FreeBSD vt consoles accept relative mouse events through /dev/consolectl, not
true tablet absolute-position events. The default absolute mode emulates tablet
mapping by translating the pen target into bounded relative movement over a
1280x800 console framebuffer.

When x201t_wacomd_console_eraser_mode=scroll, vertical eraser-side movement
emits mouse wheel/Z-axis events instead of pointer motion. Lower
x201t_wacomd_console_eraser_scroll_scale values make scrolling more sensitive.
Plain vt(4) scrollback behavior still depends on what consumes console mouse
wheel events.

For a console-only setup without the Xorg/uinput backend:

  sysrc x201t_wacomd_uinput_enable=NO
  sysrc x201t_wacomd_console_enable=YES

This port can be built without Xorg support:

  make OPTIONS_UNSET=XORG install clean

That installs only the daemon and rc.d service. Use it for minimal console-only
FreeBSD setups.

When built with the default XORG option, the port installs this Xorg tuning
sample:

  %%PREFIX%%/etc/X11/xorg.conf.d/70-x201t-uinput-wacom.conf.sample

pkg(8) activates it as 70-x201t-uinput-wacom.conf when that file does not
already exist. If you remove or replace the active config, keep the sample
available for reference.

Start x201t_wacomd before SDDM/Xorg, then restart the graphical session.
Verify with:

  xinput list
  service x201t_wacomd status

Expected Xorg devices:

  X201 Tablet ISDv4 Pen stylus
  X201 Tablet ISDv4 Pen eraser

Operational notes:

  * Run service status checks as root, or through sudo. The daemon pidfile is
    root-owned, so unprivileged service status checks may report incorrectly.

      sudo service x201t_wacomd status

  * Do not leave executable backup copies in %%PREFIX%%/etc/rc.d. FreeBSD runs
    every executable rc.d script found there. A backup such as
    x201t_wacomd.old or x201t_wacomd.pre-console can start an older daemon
    first, hold /dev/cuau2 open, and prevent the packaged service from starting
    with the current console options.
EOM
}
]
